# ME8 / Mobility C2 — Pre-ship gate (pack time only)

## Do not confuse with no-nag

- **Never** open ordinary sessions with SOS ledger / TOTP “Ship parked” nags.
- SOS ledger = PASS — do not re-ask.
- This rule is **only** when the user asks to **ship / pack / customer pack / CREATE ship / packing checklist / send to client / PH KR delivery zip**.

## When user asks to ship

1. Read and enforce:  
   `C:\Users\user\Desktop\Enterprise Mobility\ME8-INTERNAL\ship-desk\PRE-SHIP-GATE-CHECKLIST.md`
2. Immediately print **Section A — One-screen summary** from that file (the PRE-SHIP GATE block).
3. Do **not** declare “ready to send” until these are verified or user explicitly skips smoke:
   - Bundled Node **22+**
   - Ship deps include **multer** (and synced ME8 deps)
   - Zip **root** has Install + Start bats + README + APK (if VC)
   - Signed license, no private key
   - Login + change-password **example hint** in the build
   - Desk smoke: Start → `global`/`global123` on clean port (or user says skip)
4. Reminds at pack time also: `FM_TOTP_SUSPENDED` must be off for real customer ship.
5. If rebuild fails mid-way, **do not zip** a half folder (missing root bats = ship fail).

## When user is not shipping

Stay silent on this checklist.
